      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ اَلْمُحْرِمِ يَشُدُّ اَلْهِمْيَانَ فِي وَسَطِهِ فَقَالَ «نَعَمْ وَ مَا خَيْرُهُ بَعْدَ نَفَقَتِهِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.2645 - Ibn Faddal narrated from Yunus ibn Ya'qub, who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a Muhrim tying a belt (himyan) around his waist.\nImam (as) said: \"Yes, and what is better than securing his money?\""
        ]
      }
